# Blog & Content

## Adding a Post

1. Create `content/posts/{slug}.md` — slug becomes the URL (`/blog/{slug}`)
2. Include YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
title: "Post Title"
date: "2026-06-18"
summary: "One-line description for SEO and cards"
tags: ["Tag1", "Tag2"]
---
```

3. Posts are read at build time via `lib/blog.ts` (no external markdown library)

## Supported Markdown

`MarkdownRenderer` is custom and limited. Supported syntax:

- `##` / `###` headings, paragraphs, `---` dividers
- `**bold**`, `` `inline code` ``, `[text](url)` links
- Fenced code blocks with language tag
- Blockquotes (`>`)

Do not use features outside this set (tables, footnotes, HTML embeds) without extending the renderer first.

## Article Pages

- Server Components with `generateStaticParams()` and `generateMetadata()`
- Next.js 15: `params` is a Promise — always `await params`

```tsx
interface PageProps {
  params: Promise<{ slug: string }>;
}

export default async function BlogPostPage({ params }: PageProps) {
  const { slug } = await params;
  // ...
}
```

- Use `jetbrainsMono` font class on blog pages; accent color `#e8390d` for metadata icons
